getElement

private <E> void getElement(org.w3c.dom.Element e,
                            java.util.HashMap<java.lang.Integer,E> map,
                            java.util.List<E> res)
This generic function is used to parse an element describing the values for an argument of a call analysis (result of a points-to). It is used for generic object results.

Type Parameters:
E - type parameter describing the kind on element we are trying to find
Parameters:
e - The element of the DOM tree of the result file we are parsing
map - a map translating refnode references in actual graph nodes.
res - The list where we store the elements found
